      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Mile specialist HI MANAMEISJEFF NZ (2) has been freshened since coming from a wider barrier and beating a good field in the Group 2 Light Horse Free For All over the carnival. That took his record at this circuit and distance to a phenomenal 11 from 15 and he has the speed to take full advantage of the low draw. Clearly the one to beat. There was plenty to like about the resuming effort of MIKI PINS NZ (3) when he came from wider to miss by a nose at this circuit and distance. Proven second-up and draws well so looks a solid each way option. STENO (1) did a great job to come from the outside barrier and miss by a nose last start. Must be respected from the inside draw. PINSEEKER NZ (4) was beaten only 3.7m from a much wider draw last start and had won two of his other three attempts at this circuit and distance. RIPP (10) draws deep but is going well having come from the second line to win his last two outings at Bathurst.",
